      <div class="p-4 mb-2 rounded-3 bg-light">
        <div class="container-fluid py-5">
          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p class="fs-5">Welcome to our study on <strong>Split Consensus</strong>, a study to know opinions. Please keep in mind that there are no correct/incorrect answers. 
          Personal information such as your name or contacts will not be asked and your individual answers will not be shared whatsoever. The aim of this experiment is to study people who share common beliefs. 
          You can opt to not participate in this study if you don't want to:
          <ol class="fs-5">
            <li>Manifest your political beliefs (anonymously) </li>
            <li>Identify your gender (anonymously)</li>
            <li>Identify the country where you were born (anonymously)</li>
          </ol>
          </p>
          <p class="fs-5">This study will ask 14 different execrises that reflect your opinions on certain matters. 
          For each question, you may be asked to order certain options, give an estimate or categorise options based the question provided at the top your screen.
          From this study, we want to better understand how independent opinions from multiple 
          participants can be aggregated to classify them into various groups. 
          This study should take between 15 - 20 minutes to complete.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 mb-2 rounded-3 bg-light fs-5">
        <div class="container-fluid py-5">
          <h2 class= "py-2">Task</h2>
          You will be assigned 14 exercises where you will be asked to either order the images based on the criteria provided, categorise options based on some criteria or give numerical estimations. You will be given 90 seconds to answer the categorising and numerical estimation questions, and 60 seconds to answer the ordering questions. Please try your best to complete the questions before the timer runs out.
          <br>
          <br>
          Questions may be:
          <ul>
          <li>Drag and drop the given elements into the given areas according to a certain property</li>
          <li>Order the following images/elements</li>
          <li>Drag the sliders to indicate the percentage</li>
          </ul>
          </p>
          <p>
          Please answer all the questions to the best of your ability. If for whatever reason you do not answer all of the questions for a task, 
          you will be prompted to try again with the remaining time that you have left. 
        
          </p>
          <p> <span class="text-danger">NOTE:</span> Your compensation will not be affected by your performance. 
          If you are unsure about a certain question, we ask that you please answer it to the best of your ability. 

          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
            <div class="p-4 mb-2 rounded-3 bg-light fs-5">
        <div class="container-fluid py-5">
        <h1 class= "py-2">When Finished...</h1>
